This paper is about detecting Android malware using behavioral analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to build models from the sequences of API calls, which could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of designing robust tools that can operate for long periods of time without the need for modifications, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses Markov chains to model the sequences of API calls, which could be classified under data structures (cs.DS).
